\"374\" idm_id=\"000045263\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"the_pledge_of_allegiance_topg_1\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" hclass=\"headword\" id=\"the_pledge_of_allegiance_h_1\" htag=\"h1\"><span class=\"st\" id=\"the_pledge_of_allegiance_st_1\">the</span> Pledge of Allegiance</h1> <span class=\"pos\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"pos\">noun</span><span class=\"phonetics\"> <div class=\"phons_br\" geo=\"br\" htag=\"div\" hclass=\"phons_br\" wd=\"Pledge of Allegiance\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-uk icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron/p/ple/pledg/pledge_of_allegiance_1_gb_2.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/uk_pron_ogg/p/ple/pledg/pledge_of_allegiance_1_gb_2.ogg\" title=\"Pledge of Allegiance pronunciation\n                    English\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə ˌpledʒ əv əˈliːdʒəns/</span></div> <div class=\"phons_n_am\" hclass=\"phons_n_am\" wd=\"Pledge of Allegiance\" htag=\"div\" geo=\"n_am\"><div class=\"sound audio_play_button pron-us icon-audio\" data-src-mp3=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron/p/ple/pledg/pledge_of_allegiance_1_us_3.mp3\" data-src-ogg=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/media/english/us_pron_ogg/p/ple/pledg/pledge_of_allegiance_1_us_3.ogg\" title=\"Pledge of Allegiance pronunciation\n                    American\" style=\"cursor: pointer\" valign=\"top\">&nbsp;</div><span class=\"phon\">/ðə ˌpledʒ əv əˈliːdʒəns/</span></div></span><span class=\"grammar\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"grammar\">[singular]</span></div><a class=\"responsive_display_inline_on_smartphone link-right\" href=\"#relatedentries\">\n                            jump to other results\n                        </a></div></div><ol class=\"sense_single\" htag=\"ol\"><li class=\"sense\" htag=\"li\" id=\"pledgeofallegiance_sng_1\" hclass=\"sense\"><span class=\"sensetop\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"sensetop\"><span class=\"def\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"def\">a formal promise to be <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/loyal\" title=\"loyal definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">loyal</span></a> to the US, which Americans make standing in front of the flag with their right hand on their heart</span></span><ul class=\"examples\" htag=\"ul\" hclass=\"examples\"><li class=\"\" htag=\"li\"><span class=\"x\">The children recited the Pledge of Allegiance.</span></li></ul><div class=\"collapse\" hclass=\"collapse\" htag=\"div\"><span class=\"unbox\" source=\"ald9_guide\" unbox=\"cult\" id=\"pledgeofallegiance_unbox_1\"><span class=\"box_title\">Culture</span><span class=\"body\"><span class=\"p\">The words are: ‘I pledge allegiance to the flag of the United States of America and to the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/republic\" title=\"republic definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">republic</span></a> for which it stands, one nation under God, <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/indivisible\" title=\"indivisible definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">indivisible</span></a>, with <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/liberty_1\" title=\"liberty definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">liberty</span></a> and justice for all.’ It was first published in 1892 in the magazine <span class=\"ebi\">Youth's Companion</span> and written by the journalist Francis Bellamy. <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/congress#congress_sng_2\" title=\"Congress definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Congress</span></a> added the words ‘under God’ in 1954 and this has caused a lot of argument. In 2002, in the case of <span class=\"ei\">Newdow v United States Congress</span>, a <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/san-francisco\" title=\"San Francisco definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">San Francisco</span></a> court decided that the added words were against the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/constitution#constitution_sng_1\" title=\"Constitution definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Constitution</span></a>, but this decision was rejected by the <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-supreme-court\" title=\"Supreme Court definition\"><span class=\"ndv\">Supreme Court</span></a>. Many American children say the pledge each morning at school and adults also often do this on formal public occasions.</span></span></span></div>    \n</li></ol><span class=\"dictlink-g\"><span class=\"dictlink\">See <a class=\"Ref\" href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/american_english/the-pledge-of-allegiance\" title=\" definition in American English\n \"><span class=\"xh\">the Pledge of Allegiance</span></a> in the Oxford Advanced American Dictionary</span></span><div class=\"pron-link\">Check pronunciation:\n                        <a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/pronunciation/english/the-pledge-of-allegiance\">the Pledge of Allegiance</a></div></div>\n","matches":[],"relatives":[],"nearBys":["pledge verb","pledge noun","the Pledge of Allegiance noun","plenary adjective","plenary noun"]},{"name":"pledge","pos":"noun","content":"<div class=\"entry\" sum=\"717\" hclass=\"entry\" hlength=\"6\" id=\"pledge_2\" htag=\"section\" sk=\"pledge::2\" idm_id=\"000045262\"><div class=\"top-container\"><div class=\"top-g\" id=\"pledge_topg_2\"><div class=\"webtop\"><h1 class=\"headword\" id=\"pledge_h_2\" ox5000=\"y\" htag=\"h1\" hclass=\"headword\">pledge</h1> <span class=\"pos\" htag=\"span\" hclass=\"pos\">noun</span><div class=\"symbols\" hclass=\"symbols\" htag=\"div\"><a href=\"https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/wordlists/oxfo